<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer8211276775568173299">Ruth Ozeki (born in New Haven, Connecticut) is a Japanese American novelist. She is the daughter of anthropologist Floyd Lounsbury.<br/><br/>Ozeki published her debut novel, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12349.My_Year_of_Meats' title='My Year of Meats' rel='nofollow noopener'>My Year of Meats</a>, in 1998. She followed up with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/917346.All_Over_Creation' title='All Over Creation' rel='nofollow noopener'>All Over Creation</a> in 2003. Her new novel, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15811545.A_Tale_for_the_Time_Being' title='A Tale for the Time Being' rel='nofollow noopener'>A Tale for the Time Being</a>, was published on March 12, 2013. <br/><br/>She is married to Canadian land artist <a href='http://www.oliverk.org' rel='nofollow noopener'>Oliver Kellhammer</a>, and the couple divides their</span>
  <span id="freeText8211276775568173299" style="display:none">Ruth Ozeki (born in New Haven, Connecticut) is a Japanese American novelist. She is the daughter of anthropologist Floyd Lounsbury.<br /><br />Ozeki published her debut novel, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12349.My_Year_of_Meats" title="My Year of Meats" rel="nofollow noopener">My Year of Meats</a>, in 1998. She followed up with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/917346.All_Over_Creation" title="All Over Creation" rel="nofollow noopener">All Over Creation</a> in 2003. Her new novel, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15811545.A_Tale_for_the_Time_Being" title="A Tale for the Time Being" rel="nofollow noopener">A Tale for the Time Being</a>, was published on March 12, 2013. <br /><br />She is married to Canadian land artist <a href="http://www.oliverk.org" rel="nofollow noopener">Oliver Kellhammer</a>, and the couple divides their time between New York City and Vancouver.</span>
